      "form_guide": "",
      "comment": "COME AND SEE (3) has a fair record and proved too classy last time to win by 2 lengths at Geelong in a handy 22.74 beating Aussie Wagyu. Looks to have an edge on most of these. WESTERN'S NASIAH (2) missed the frame latest when fifth at The Meadows (30.40) but was a winner five back in the second best time of the program. Solid record here at the distance winning two races. Form is hard to fault from this box, with a win and two minor placings from three starts. Key runner who gets his chance to atone. NAUGHTY NORM (6) goes very well this course and distance starting 10 times for four wins and three minors. Below best last time at Warrnambool (22.34) in a Free For All, finishing a 5 length fifth. Makes strong appeal on best. SOMETHING GOOD (1) scored last time and can measure up again.",
